				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Finally finished the improved r2 layout and assembled the first board.<br />The new layout adds a microcontroller, USB, switching regulator, RGB status led, and many small improvements.<br /><br />The biggest change is the microcontroller, which does all the heavy lifting instead of the GB CPU.<br />The microcontroller and FPGA can be programmed via USB, so no more fiddling with the JTAG adapter and<br />programming the FPGA now only takes 3s instead of &gt;30.<br /><br />I'm now adapting the FPGA firmware to the new hardware. Many of the firmware blocks are now obsolete, making<br />the firmware more compact. But I still have to write a new interface between uC and FPGA to load files into memory.<br /><br /><img src="http://i.imgur.com/18Bi09a.jpg" alt="Image" /></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

